phy, science, morality, and art; what emerges is a view of humans as aesthetic, meaning-making creatures who draw on their deepest physical processes to make sense of the world around them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAesthetics. 0aEthics. 0aExperience. 0aMeaning (Philosophy). 0aPhilosophy and cognitive science. 0aPragmatism. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  acognitive science.  aembodiment.  alanguage.  ameaning.  ametaphor.  amorality.  apragmatism.  areasoning.  aunderstanding.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226539133423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226539133/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles